name: nrel-pysam
summary: national renewable energy laboratory's system advisor model python wrapper
documentation_summary: The HTML text provides documentation for PySAM version 5.0.0, a Python package developed by the National Renewable Energy Laboratory (NREL) for the System Advisor Model (SAM). It is part of the SAM Software Development Kit (SDK) and is built on the PySSC wrapper for the SAM Simulation Core (SSC) API. The documentation covers installation instructions, getting started guides, an overview of PySAM, details on importing inputs from SAM, accessing SAM defaults, working with variables, PySAM functions, and building PySAM for NREL DAO-Tk. It also includes a list of SAM configurations and SSC compute modules, along with information on building PySAM from source.
